ressions into the join condition, which can help reduce the amount of data processed in the join.\n\n### Step-by-Step Transformation:\n\n1. **Apply AGGREGATE_CASE_TO_FILTER**:\n   - Convert the `CASE` statements in the `SUM` functions to filtered aggregates.\n   - Original:\n     ```sql\n     sum(case\n         when o_orderpriority = \'1-URGENT\'\n             or o_orderpriority = \'2-HIGH\'\n             then 1\n         else 0\n     end) as high_line_count,\n     sum(case\n         when o_orderpriority <> \'1-URGENT\'\n             and o_orderpriority <> \'2-HIGH\'\n             then 1\n         else 0\n     end) as low_line_count\n     ```\n   - Transformed:\n     ```sql\n     sum(o_orderpriority = \'1-URGENT\' or o_orderpriority = \'2-HIGH\') as high_line_count,\n     sum(o_orderpriority <> \'1-URGENT\' and o_orderpriority <> \'2-HIGH\') as low_line_count\n     ```\n\n2. **Apply FILTER_INTO_JOIN**:\n   - Push the filter conditions into the join to reduce the data processed.\n   - The filter conditions on `lineitem` can be applied before the join to reduce the number of rows joined.\n\n### Final Optimized Query:\n```sql\nselect\n    l_shipmode,\n    sum(o_orderpriority = \'1-URGENT\' or o_orderpriority = \'2-HIGH\') as high_line_count,\n    sum(o_orderpriority <> \'1-URGENT\' and o_orderpriority <> \'2-HIGH\') as low_line_count\nfrom\n    (select * from lineitem where l_shipmode in (\'SHIP\', \'RAIL\')\n     and l_commitdate < l_receiptdate\n     and l_shipdate < l_commitdate\n     and l_receiptdate >= date \'1995-01-01\'\n     and l_receiptdate < date \'1995-01-01\' + interval \'1\' year) as filtered_lineitem\njoin\n    orders\non\n    o_orderkey = l_orderkey\ngroup by\n    l_shipmode\norder by\n    l_shipmode\nlimit 1;\n```\n\n### Selected Rewrite Rules:\n```python\n[\n    "AGGREGATE_CASE_TO_FILTER",\n    "FILTER_INTO_JOIN"\n]\n```', 'time': 6.441218614578247}
